RICHIE, POTSIE & RALPH:
♪ Glorious, victorious ♪

01:22.249 --> 01:25.048
♪ One keg of suds
for the four of us ♪

01:25.185 --> 01:28.985
♪ Singing glory be to God
that there are no more of us ♪

01:29.122 --> 01:31.921
♪ As we could drink it
all alone! ♪

01:32.059 --> 01:34.152
♪ All alone. ♪

01:34.294 --> 01:36.126
I love college life.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.528
Drinking songs, climbing
greased poles, panty raids.

01:39.666 --> 01:41.635
I love being a man.

01:41.768 --> 01:44.294
What are you guys
so happy about?

01:44.438 --> 01:46.235
You're starting Hell Week.

01:46.373 --> 01:47.704
I get the woolies just thinking

01:47.841 --> 01:49.639
of all the terrible things
they're gonna make you do.

01:49.776 --> 01:54.180
Al, we're joining the best frat
on campus, Phi Kappa Nu.

01:54.314 --> 01:56.112
Yeah, it's got
the-the highest grade standing.

01:56.249 --> 01:57.774
It's got the best athletes.

01:57.918 --> 01:59.351
It's got
the best fraternity house.

01:59.486 --> 02:00.886
You don't just goof around.

02:01.021 --> 02:02.648
Like, all afternoon,
we've been out collecting toys

02:02.789 --> 02:03.847
for underprivileged children.

02:03.991 --> 02:05.982
Ah, fraternities.

02:06.126 --> 02:09.151
I wish I was...
ten years younger.

02:09.295 --> 02:10.661
Yeah.

02:14.201 --> 02:17.000
Hey.

02:22.643 --> 02:25.077
Let me tell you something,
my little gladiola.

02:25.212 --> 02:27.647
Don't you brood,
'cause once I touch your car,

02:27.781 --> 02:32.651
I'm gonna get it in
as good of shape as... you are.

02:32.786 --> 02:34.345
- RALPH: Fonz! -POTSIE: Hey,
Fonzie, how you doing?

02:34.488 --> 02:35.682
Hey, look who's over there.

02:35.822 --> 02:38.519
- If it ain't Potsie
and Ralph and Richie. -Yeah.

02:38.659 --> 02:39.717
See, there's my friends.

02:39.860 --> 02:41.828
Listen, you remember Boom Boom?

02:41.962 --> 02:45.193
Yeah, she was, uh,
last month's, uh, centerfold

02:45.332 --> 02:48.063
<i>'m All About Roller Derby.</i>

02:48.201 --> 02:49.294
Oh, yeah.

02:49.436 --> 02:50.870
I saw her on television.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.495
These are my buddies.
They're college men.

02:52.639 --> 02:54.972
Very intellectual
fraternity boys...

02:55.108 --> 02:57.771
dressed like... bowling pins.

02:58.812 --> 03:00.405
Well, Fonz...

03:00.547 --> 03:03.380
Fonz, we got to wear the
beanies, because it's Hell Week.

03:03.517 --> 03:04.814
Oh, right. See that?

03:04.951 --> 03:06.578
The whole week,
they're gonna eat goldfish,

03:06.720 --> 03:09.519
get paddled upside one down
their body, down the other.

03:09.656 --> 03:11.920
- Yeah. -Eating goldfish.
Fun stuff, Fonz.

03:12.059 --> 03:14.186
Yeah, but once
we get through Hell Week,

03:14.327 --> 03:16.455
then we're fraternity brothers
for life.

03:16.596 --> 03:18.223
- Brothers! -Brothers!
- FONZIE: Right, right.

03:18.365 --> 03:20.197
Well, I got no time
for college frolicking.

03:20.333 --> 03:24.031
You know, see, her '51 MG
got vandalized on the street,

03:24.171 --> 03:25.195
stripped to the bone.

03:25.338 --> 03:26.567
OTHERS:
Aw!

03:26.707 --> 03:28.140
Soto speak. Yeah.

03:29.509 --> 03:30.442
Do me a favor, okay?

03:30.577 --> 03:31.669
Here's a dime.

03:31.812 --> 03:33.973
Go right over there--
that a girl--

03:34.114 --> 03:35.980
and call Happy Harry's Garage.

03:36.116 --> 03:37.550
You got that? Right?

03:37.684 --> 03:39.015
Ask him for a carburetor.

03:39.152 --> 03:41.143
Here you go.

03:43.056 --> 03:45.116
I'm gonna get her a new chassis.

03:45.258 --> 03:46.954
Not that she needs one.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.333
There's the president of PKN.
More fun, guys.

03:54.468 --> 03:56.663
Got any good pledges this year?

03:56.803 --> 03:59.363
Uh, well, there's Myers.
He's not bad. Johnson.

04:00.907 --> 04:02.136
Cunningham I like.

04:02.275 --> 04:04.540
I'm not so sure about Malph
and Weber, though, uh...

04:04.678 --> 04:05.736
Malph and Weber, huh?

04:05.879 --> 04:08.075
Hey, and the pledge master,
Terrible Tom.

04:08.215 --> 04:10.046
He's all right.
Come on, let's go.

04:10.183 --> 04:11.412
- Hey, guys.
- Hi, fellas.

04:11.551 --> 04:12.780
- Hi.
- All right, hi.

04:12.919 --> 04:14.114
We got to get back
to the frat house,

04:14.254 --> 04:15.380
set things up
for the dance tonight.

04:15.522 --> 04:16.853
- RALPH: Yes, sir.
- RICHIE: All right.

04:16.990 --> 04:18.185
Where are the other pledges?

04:18.325 --> 04:19.622
Uh, they're not here yet, Brad.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.523
Let me have some fun
with the ones we got, huh?

04:21.661 --> 04:23.288
You know, sort of
whip 'em into shape.

04:23.430 --> 04:24.829
They're all yours.

04:24.965 --> 04:26.592
-(throat clearing)
- All right, now, pledges,

04:26.733 --> 04:30.101
all I want you to do is deliver
these party invitations

04:30.237 --> 04:31.704
to the Iota girls.

04:31.838 --> 04:34.205
RALPH & POTSIE:
Yes, sir, sir!

04:34.341 --> 04:36.138
- RICHIE: Uh...
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.540
Those are airmail.

04:38.678 --> 04:40.408
Man your planes, pledges!

04:40.547 --> 04:42.037
(making nasal, buzzing sounds)

04:42.182 --> 04:43.741
Malph, there's an Iota at 6:00.

04:43.884 --> 04:45.943
-(making nasal buzzing sounds)
- Weber, hit the air.

04:46.086 --> 04:48.179
Cunningham, you're sputtering.

04:48.321 --> 04:49.653
Refuel!

04:49.790 --> 04:51.018
Oh!

04:51.158 --> 04:52.523
(nasal humming)

04:52.659 --> 04:54.320
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

04:54.461 --> 04:55.553
- Whoa! Whoa!
- Zih.

04:55.695 --> 04:57.527
- Yeah, ziz, ziz, zih, right.
-(board slapping)

04:57.664 --> 04:59.155
Cunningham,
let me ask you a question.

04:59.299 --> 05:02.325
Is this the way that college
is preparing you for life?

05:02.469 --> 05:03.629
(board slapping)

05:03.770 --> 05:05.397
Oh, Fonz, I realize
this looks a little silly.

05:05.539 --> 05:07.029
-(nasal buzzing continues)
- Yeah. -Oh.

05:07.174 --> 05:08.641
- It may be silly...
-(board slapping)

05:08.775 --> 05:10.607
...but-but we got to prove that
we're worthy of being PKNs.

05:10.744 --> 05:12.303
That's the whole point
of all this stuff.

05:12.445 --> 05:13.936
And, yeah,
it is very important to us.

05:14.080 --> 05:15.104
Yeah, I'll tell you something.

05:15.248 --> 05:16.739
I didn't realize
how important it was.

05:16.883 --> 05:18.351
Go back to being a bumblebee.

05:18.485 --> 05:19.975
(board slapping)

05:20.120 --> 05:22.247
-(nasal buzzing continues)
- I'm a plane.

05:22.389 --> 05:23.856
No, you're not.
I know planes.

05:23.990 --> 05:25.754
I've got a Min-engine model
over here.

05:25.892 --> 05:27.360
(Fonzie laughs)

05:27.494 --> 05:30.190
(buzzing continues)

05:30.330 --> 05:32.424
BRAD:
That's enough.

05:32.566 --> 05:34.329
- Okay, all right. -We got
to get 'em back to the house.

05:34.467 --> 05:35.696
We'll take care
of the other pledges later.

05:35.835 --> 05:37.098
- Let's go, pledges.
- Yes, sir.

05:37.237 --> 05:39.706
Ah... let's go as ducks.

05:39.839 --> 05:41.364
More fun, right?

05:41.508 --> 05:42.998
Get quacking, pledgers.

05:43.143 --> 05:44.736
(Richie, Potsie and Ralph
making quacking sounds)

05:44.878 --> 05:47.006
First one back gets a bowl
of bird seed.

05:47.147 --> 05:48.273
Wow, a prize!

05:48.415 --> 05:50.212
(quacking resumes)

05:50.350 --> 05:51.476
(board slaps)

